      • setServiceId

        public final void setServiceId(int serviceId)
        Description copied from interface: ServiceObject
        Specifies an id of the service with which is this service object associated.

        Note, that changing of this id should not be permitted if it has been already specified, so service object implementations are allowed to throw an exception if such action is to be performed.

        Specified by:
        setServiceId in interface ServiceObject
        Parameters:
        serviceId - The desired service id.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - If service id has been already specified for this service object.
        See Also:
        ServiceObject.getServiceId()

      • setRequestId

        public final void setRequestId(@NonNull
                               String requestId)
        Description copied from interface: ServiceObject
        Sets an id of the request with which is this service object associated.

        Note, that changing of this id should not be permitted if it has been already specified, so service object implementations are allowed to throw an exception if such action is to be performed.

        Specified by:
        setRequestId in interface ServiceObject
        Parameters:
        requestId - The desired request id. Should be unique among all requests made for a specific service or better, unique among all requests made through services API to really uniquely identify a desired request.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - If request id has been already specified for this service object.
        See Also:
        ServiceObject.getRequestId()
